    {
      "id": "PopularPost40720",
      "post_content": "No, discarding does NOT count as \"damage.\" Consider the Basking Rootwalla. It has a Madness cost of 0, which means if you discard it, you can play it directly for no mana cost . . . and no rule I have ever seen equates the drawing or discarding of cards with damage . . . ",
